"subtopic": "1. Introduction",
"content": "• Experiential Learning · Analysing\n\n• O describe rules for making ray diagrams for spherical mirror; distinguish between real and virtual images.\n• Display a scientific attitude while making models.\n• Communicate logical reasoning and explanations effectively using scientific terms.\n• Speed of light is extraordinarily large at $ 3 \\times 10^{8} $ m/s in vacuum or air.\n• Finally, you will study the action of a prism and dispersion caused by a prism.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Dispersion — associated with : Splitting of white light into its constituent seven colours on passing through a dispersive medium, e.g., a glass prism\n• Prism — associated with : A transparent material bound by two plane refracting faces inclined at an angle\n• Spherical mirror — associated with : A slice taken out from a hollow glass sphere and silvered on one side so that reflection takes place from the other side\n• Virtual image — associated with : Image formed when light rays do not actually meet but appear to meet\n• Light — a form of energy which travels in a straight line",
"source": "icse",
"examTip": "Read this section, then practice linked questions before moving on.",
