"content": "The seven-coloured rays obtained in the spectrum of white light produced by a glass prism of be recombined into white light again if these coloured rays are made to pass through another prism which is identical to the…\n\n• Dispersion is associated with : Splitting of white light into its constituent seven colours on passing through a dispersive medium, e.g., a glass prism.\n• Spectrum is associated with : The band of seven colours obtained as a result of dispersion of white light.\n• O describe dispersion of white light by a prism into constituent colours.\n• Recombination of seven constituent colours of white light spectrum.\n• A glass slab is a rectangular block of glass through which light can be refracted.\n• Aim: To show dispersion of white light through a glass prism.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Dispersion — associated with : Splitting of white light into its constituent seven colours on passing through a dispersive medium, e.g., a glass prism\n• Prism — associated with : A transparent material bound by two plane refracting faces inclined at an angle\n• Spectrum — associated with : The band of seven colours obtained as a result of dispersion of white light\n• Light — a form of energy which travels in a straight line\n\nAlso know:\n• Dispersion of light happens because sunlight is made up of seven different colours.\n• Consequently, white light is split up into its seven constituent colours and a spectrum is formed.\n• Seven colours of the spectrum may be remembered by the acronym VIBGYOR.\n• Aim: To show recombination of seven colours of spectrum to form white light.",
"source": "icse",
