"subtopic": "16. E. Define these terms",
"content": "1. Coefficient of linear expansion\n\n• 0 describe, linear, area (superficial) and volume expansion.\n• Linear expansion: If the given solid is in the form of a rod or a wire, then on heating, its length increases and the thermal expansion is called linear expansion.\n• Force coefficient of linear expansion of a solid in the form of a rod or wire is defined as the increase in its length per unit original length per degree rise in temperature.\n• Area (superficial) expansion: If the given solid is in the form of a thin sheet, then on heating, its surface area increases and the thermal expansion is called area expansion or superficial expansion.\n• Mathematically, it is observed that $\\Delta V \\propto V \\Delta T$ or $\\Delta V = V \\gamma \\Delta T$ where $\\gamma$ is a constant known as the coefficient of volume expansion of the given solid material.\n• Coefficient of volume expansion of copper, $\\gamma = \\frac{\\Delta V}{V \\times \\Delta T}$.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Thermal expansion — an increase in the size of a substance on heating\n• Linear expansion: If the given solid — in the form of a rod or a wire, then on heating, its length increases and the thermal expansion is called linear expansion\n• Area (superficial) expansion: If the given solid — in the form of a thin sheet, then on heating, its surface area increases and the thermal expansion is called area expansion or superficial expansion\n• Mathematically, it — found that $ \\Delta A \\propto A \\Delta T $\n• Volume expansion — defined as When a bulk solid like a cube, cuboid, sphere, cylinder, etc., is heated, its volume increases and the thermal expansion is called volume expansion. The amount of\n\nAlso know:\n• Coefficient of linear expansion of copper is ___ than that of iron.\n• Coefficient of linear expansion (α) = ___ × coefficient of volume expansion (γ).\n• Coefficient of linear expansion of a solid is given by the formula.\n• : Expansion of solid in length on heating.",
