"type": "note",
"subtopic": "1. Introduction",
"content": "In previous classes, you have learnt about 'sound'. Sound is a form of energy which causes sensation of hearing in our ears. Let us recollect some important facts about sound. These are as follows:\n\n• Different types of instruments and devices are used to produce sound.\n• 》 In humans, sound is produced by the voice box (larynx) located.\n• Sound needs a medium for its propagation.\n• Sound travels with a finite speed in the given material medium.\n• Speed of sound is maximum in solids, less in liquids and the least in gases.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Sound — a form of energy which causes sensation of hearing in our ears\n• Different types of instruments and devices — used to produce sound\n• 》 In humans, sound — produced by the voice box (larynx) located\n• Speed of sound — maximum in solids, less in liquids and the least in gases\n\nAlso know:\n• Sound travels ___ in solids and ___ in gases.\n• Sound is a form of energy which can propagate through a material medium only.",
"source": "icse",
"examTip": "Read this section, then practice linked questions before moving on.",
