"subtopic": "4. Activity 4 SEL Self-Awareness",
"content": "Aim: To show that vibration frequency of a string increases on increasing the tension\n\n• Materials Required: A sonometer arrangement, steel hanger and slotting weights.\n• Materials Required is defined as A sonometer arrangement, steel hanger and slotting weights.\n• Procedure: A sonometer consists of a hollow wooden box about 1 m long, 10 cm broad and 10 cm height.\n• Initially, the weight of 1 kg on the hanger.\n• Then, increase the weight put on hanger to 1.5 kg.\n• Observation and Conclusion: Due to weight suspended with wire, a tension T is developed in the wire, which is equal to weight of hanger and slotted weights.",
"explanation": "Definitions:\n• Sound — a form of energy which causes sensation of hearing in our ears\n• Frequency — usually represented by symbol v (Greek letter nu)\n\nAlso know:\n• A sound produced by a particular musical instrument is usually called a tone.\n• A tuning fork is a U-shaped metallic device which consists.\n• Generally, tuning forks of frequencies 256, 288, 320, 342, 384, 426, 480 and 512 Hz are available in school laboratories.\n• Tuning forks generally correspond to the eight tones of Indian musical scale in which the keynote (the lowest frequency) is taken as 256 Hz.",
