"topicId": "ch8-electricity",
"type": "note",
"subtopic": "8. Activity 2 SEL Self-Management",
"content": "Aim: To show electrification by rubbing\n\n• Materials Required: A plastic scale or a comb or a pen, tiny bits of paper, woollen or nylon material.\n• Materials Required is defined as A plastic scale or a comb or a pen, tiny bits of paper, woollen or nylon material.\n• Procedure: Take a plastic scale or a comb or a pen and rub it against your dry hair.\n• Observation and conclusion: The paper bits fly and stick to the plastic scale.\n• Observation and conclusion is defined as The paper bits fly and stick to the plastic scale. Why? On rubbing, the scale has acquired some charge, due to which, it attracts the bits of paper.\n• Your searchlight is now ready to work.",
